###################################################################################
############################### BUILDING GUIDELINES ###############################
###################################################################################



This document provides guidelines on how to build Zen binaries on several platforms.

>>>	Windows :
-----------------
	++ This package comes along with a Code::Blocks workspace, which contains 2 projects:
		Zen for Windows and Zen for Linux
		Just compile the Zen for Windows project, and everything shall work fine.
	++ If you want to use your own IDE, then just
		add all the files in the "scr" directory and the sub-directories, except "adllin.c".

>>>	GNU/Linux :
-------------------
	++ This package comes along with a Code::Blocks workspace, which contains 2 projects:
		Zen for Windows and Zen for Linux
		Just compile the Zen for Linux project, and everything shall work fine.
	++ If you want to use your own IDE, then just
		add all the files in the "scr" directory and the sub-directories, except "adlwin.c".

>>>	MacOS :
---------------
	++ We didn't test it yet, but it should work fine by compiling the Zen for Linux version.
	++ If you want to report a problem while trying to build it on a Mac,
		or just want to help us providing cross-platform support,
		please feel free to contact us at:
			darklinkcompany@gmail.com
			younis.bensalah02@yahoo.de



